    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a large horizontal disk and a small horizontal disk in three states. First, the large disk spins counterclockwise about a vertical axis through its center at an angular speed of omega sub 0, and the small disk is at rest centered directly above the large disk. Second, the small disk is falling down toward the large disk, which continues to spin counterclockwise at angular speed omega sub 0. Third, the two disks are in contact and rotating together at the same angular speed omega sub f.\" src=\"/images/3c33166ca2013936acc275fae3afd98e.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A large, horizontal, uniform disk is rotating freely with angular speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"omega sub 0\"><math alttext=\"omega sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> about a vertical axis at its center, as shown in the figures. A smaller uniform disk, which is less massive than the large disk, is initially at rest&nbsp;and centered directly above the large disk. At time <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"t sub 0\"><math alttext=\"t sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> the small disk is dropped down onto the large disk, and at a later time <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"t sub f\"><math alttext=\"t sub f\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>t</mi><mi>f</mi></msub></math></span></span> the two disks are rotating together at the same angular speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"omega sub f\"><math alttext=\"omega sub f\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mi>f</mi></msub></math></span></span>, which is less than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"omega sub 0\"><math alttext=\"omega sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span>. Why is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"omega sub f\"><math alttext=\"omega sub f\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mi>f</mi></msub></math></span></span> less than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"omega sub 0\"><math alttext=\"omega sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> ?</p>\n",
